#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:788
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:794
msgid "How does this plugin work?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:795
msgid "Speakable uses the Web Speech API built into modern browsers. It reads the article text aloud using system voices on the visitor's device. No external API or server required - it's completely free."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:799
msgid "Which browsers are supported?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:800
msgid "Chrome, Edge, Safari, Firefox, and Opera all support the Web Speech API. If a visitor's browser doesn't support it, a friendly fallback message is shown instead of the player."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:804
msgid "Why do voices sound different on different devices?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:805
msgid "The Web Speech API uses voices installed on the visitor's operating system. Windows, macOS, Android, and iOS each have different built-in voices. The voice you select in settings is a preference - if it's not available on a visitor's device, their browser default is used."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:809
msgid "Can I use this with custom post types?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:810
msgid "Yes! Go to Speakable > Settings > Display tab and enable any public post type. The player will appear on singular views for all enabled types."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:814
msgid "Does this plugin slow down my site?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:815
msgid "No. The plugin loads a single lightweight CSS and JS file only on pages where the player is displayed. There are no external API calls, no server-side processing, and no impact on page load speed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:819
msgid "How do I use the REST API?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-speakable-admin.php:820
msgid "The plugin provides public REST API endpoints for React Native and mobile apps. Enable it from Speakable > Settings > API tab, then check the endpoint URLs and documentation. No authentication required."
msgstr ""

